Apr 3 2009 	Great Room Friendly Service Fantastic Location	Stayed here for 7 nights in February - reception was very friendly and offered a choice of rooms. The room was very large and comfortable, and the daily service left it immaculate. The lobby area is still under renovations, but that may be why the price was so good. The hotel location is outstanding if you want to be downtown (one block from Union Square) and as it is on the tram line it is easy to get around. The tram line adds a little noise if your room is lower down, but the rooms are well insulated for sound, so that wasn't a problem. For my stay the room was less than $100 U.S. a night...very hard to beat. Did not use the restaurant, but there are good breakfast places nearby, and who wants to eat in a hotel when you are in a city with so many good restaurants?	
Mar 28 2009 	It is changing to a Marriott on April 1 2009- Needs some fine tuning	We stayed for 9 nights at Hotel 480. The first and most important thing to know is that the lobby and front door area is under construction. This was not a big deal for me as I only spent about 30 seconds in those areas each day. As it was under construction we got a great deal, (94.00 per night - expedia). The construction work is only done through the day, so for most people that is not a proplem unless you are a very late sleeper.The rooms are very nice, appears to be almost all new carpet, furniture and fixtures. Our room had two proplems. The first was that even though we were on the 19th floor there are no window curtains on the floor to ceiling windows in the bathroom. Not a big deal until the workers/window washers come by (they did, then a mad dash to become fully dressed). Really the hotel should have some sort of curtains or covering, a person with a good telescope in another building could be getting a good show.The other issue is the old story of chasing the hot water in the morning. I thought all hotels had beaten this proplem. The showers in the morning were an ongoing problem each day we were there. Ranged from very cold to too hot, with a few moments of just right thrown in. Perhaps being on the 19th floor had a bearing, but it should not be so.The hotel has to work on this if it wants to attact the business crowd, end of story!The staff were OK, not great, not bad, cleaning staff missed a couple of things during the stay, but when spoken to it was fixed.We took the advice of another on this site and asked for a corner unit on a upper floor, good advice in regards to traffic and outside noise, (it is downtown after all), The corner unit gives you a 2nd door to close that will keep hallway noise from invading your room. (Weekends guests seem to make more noise) The only proplem with ours was that we were locked in our small hallway until I pried it open, the hardware on the frame was missing, not a big deal until there is a fire and you want to leave quickly!!Once again, Marriiott is a big company and I am sure that they will fix most of these issues. Overall it is clean and well appointed and I would stay there again.	
