Jun 2 2007 	This was one of my best stays in San Francisco! Ever!	I had read the reviews and knew this hotel was convenient, but I had no idea how exceptionally close this hotel was to shopping, dining, transportation, everything, until I got there. It was an easy walk to whatever I wanted: for example, one night I peeked in at Farallon, decided I wouldn't fit in; strolled over to Kuleto's, too packed; came back to Scala's Bistro. All within minutes. I'm still amazed at how close I was to everything.The service was excellent. The front desk was always courteous and thorough. The bellmen were beyond-the-call helpful. I don't know about other posters, but I found my bed to be very comfortable. It's not the Westin's &quot;Heavenly Bed,&quot; but every night when my head hit all four pillows, I'd be out like a light....and getting up was truly a chore. I used their aromatherapy spray and relaxation CD, too.The shower massage has six settings, which I found novel. The handicap bar in the shower seemed to be in an awkward place and I bumped it constantly. I liked that the housekeeper replenished the toiletries every day. (Hey, you'd THINK that was basic in a 4*, but that hasn't always happened!)The workout room is a little cramped, but OK if just a few people are using it. When I finished on the treadmill, there were 3 other people in there and the guy on the elliptical machine had to stop pedaling so that I could squeeze past him! It's nice to have a workout room IN the hotel, though. The machines are newish and clean; they have a water dispenser; and there's a TV in there, which I hogged. I was a little bummed out that the internet service in the business area was so expensive, but fortunately I didn't have to use it much at all. Overall, it was a VERY enjoyable stay. Kudos to the staff, who were warm and welcoming. I hope I get to stay here again! I've told all my friends about it!	
