Jun 8 2004	Not for business travelers	Here's the deal....This is an acceptable hotel for leisure travelers looking for an anonyous, safe, no-frills place to stay in an urban area...the sort of folks who plan to use the room for showering and sleeping. As a result, expect lots of pragmatic, budget-minded European tourists.For business travelers, this place is a disaster. Most rooms have no internet (imagine, no internet in SF?!?!). The lobby offers wifi, but you have to buy a $5 pass from clerks who have no idea what wifi really is. Twice the wi-fi didn't work and the clerk told me to call a number in NY! The business center consists of one multipurpose printer (fax, scanner, copier, printer all in one) which used to operate via credit card (though is now broken)...and that's it for the business center. All told, simply not very functional at all compared to even the likes of a standard Sheraton or a Marriott Courtyard.Finally, if you want a nice play to stay to impress your sweetie with luxury (e.g. a nice Westin), this is NOT your place...Very utilitarian, though clean.	
